          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-12-09 14:32:51" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>the content of that which has not been known before but which has been revealed to an in-group or restricted constituency</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>secret</Gloss>
                <Gloss>mystery</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>There is a serious problem involved in translating μυστήριον by a word which is equivalent to the English expression ‘mystery,’ for this term in English refers to a secret which people have tried to uncover but which they have failed to understand. In many instances μυστήριον is translated by a phrase meaning ‘that which was not known before,’ with the implication of its being revealed at least to some persons.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
